\begin{document}
\begin{equation*} \left \left[\frac{ \left \left({\mathrm{Dermal\;thickness\;at\;48\;or\;72\;h}}-{\mathrm{Dermal\;thickness\;at\;0\;h}}\right) \right }{{\mathrm{Dermal\;thickness\;at\;0\;h}}}\right] \right {\times}{\mathrm{100\%.}}\end{equation*}\end{document}

The slope of the elicitation response for each of the SSR-treated individuals was then used in the formula below to calculate percentage suppression of CHS: \documentclass[10pt]{article}
